tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes/diabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. Mildly decreased total CO₂ may suggest a tendency toward metabolic acidosis; clinical correlation is advised. No acute abnormalities detected. Recommend follow-up for glycemic control and assessment of acid-base status if clinically indicated.
